#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Original-style Ricci classifiers on corrected [B | K0] feature vectors.

This script applies the classifier method used in the original Ricci run to all
five manuscript tasks:

    1. non-IBD vs UC vs CD
    2. IBD vs non-IBD
    3. non-IBD vs UC
    4. non-IBD vs CD
    5. CD vs UC

Original-style classifier
-------------------------
For each task, the feature vector is:

    X_s = [B_s | K0_s]

where:

    B_s(e)  = 1 if edge e is active/present in sample s, else 0
    K0_s(e) = Ricci curvature kappa_s(e) if e is active/present, else 0

The model is:

    StandardScaler(with_mean=True, with_std=True)
        +
    L1 LogisticRegression(solver="saga", class_weight="balanced", C=0.02)

The scaler is inside the sklearn Pipeline, so in cross-validation the scaler is
fit only on the training participants of each fold and then applied to the held-
out participants. This avoids leakage while matching the original classifier
method.

Coefficient interpretation
--------------------------
Because features are standardised, coefficients are coefficients on z-scored
features. A positive K0 coefficient means that higher-than-training-average
curvature for that edge pushes toward the relevant class.

Inputs
------
The feature directory must contain:

    feature_matrix_B_K0.npz
    matched_metadata.csv
    edge_metadata.csv

These are produced by the faithful Ricci feature builder.

Outputs
-------
For each task folder:

    fold_results.csv
    aggregated_confusion_matrix.csv
    cross_validated_predictions.csv
    classification_report.txt
    latex_fold_results.tex
    latex_confusion_matrix.tex

    single_grouped_train_val_test_split.csv
    single_grouped_train_val_test_results.csv
    single_split_train_report.txt
    single_split_val_report.txt
    single_split_test_report.txt
    final_trainval_test_report.txt

    selected_coefficients_final_trainval_model.csv
    process_coefficient_table.csv
    process_realised_push_table.csv
    top_absolute_features.csv
    top_positive_features.csv / top_negative_features.csv for binary tasks
    top_positive_B_features.csv / top_positive_K0_features.csv for binary tasks
    top_negative_B_features.csv / top_negative_K0_features.csv for binary tasks

At the top output directory:

    all_task_summary.csv
    pairwise_binary_summary.csv
    latex_all_task_summary.tex
    latex_pairwise_binary_summary.tex
    latex_all_original_style_ricci_tables.tex

Notes
-----
If edge_metadata.csv contains only "Unannotated" process labels, the process
tables will be structurally correct but biologically uninformative. In that case
provide --edge-annotation-csv with edge/process annotations.
"""

